      "value": "<p>You know one handy trick for stopping a spellcaster in their magical tracks.</p><hr /><p><strong>Benefit:</strong> When you successfully cause an enemy’s spell to fail with a melee attack of opportunity, that enemy must attempt a Fortitude save equal to 10 + half the weapon’s item level + the ability modifier you used to attack with that weapon. On a failed save, the spellcaster is unable to cast any spells until the end of their next turn. Any penalty you would normally take to your weapon attack roll also applies to this DC.</p>"
